          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Election Certainty Act</b></p> <p>This bill establishes certain requirements for delivered ballots in federal elections.</p> <p>Specifically, the bill requires a ballot submitted by mail or otherwise delivered in a federal election, in order to be counted, to (1) include the signature of the voter, and (2) be received by the appropriate election official by the date of the election.</p> <p>Further, the bill requires a ballot that is delivered by a third party on behalf of a voter to include the signature of the third party. It also restricts the types of individuals who can deliver such a ballot to certain family members of the voter.</p> <p>The bill excludes absent uniformed service members and their family members from these requirements.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2020-11-24T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
